{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place onions in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sugar, red wine vinegar, water, rosemary, cinnamon stick, peppercorns, bay leaf, nutmeg, cranberries, salt and pepper and cook <nobr>12 min\/90°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.  Scrape down sides and bottom of mixing bowl with spatula.","Cook further <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula again.","Place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid to help prevent splashing and cook <nobr>15 min\/60°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Season chutney to taste and remove cinnamon sticks and bay leaf. Transfer to 2 hot clean jars with twist-off lids (500 g each) (see tip) and close immediately. Store in a cool, dry place."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g red onions, cut into halves","220 g sugar","125 g red wine vinegar","185 g water","4 sprigs fresh rosemary, needles removed from stalk","1 cinnamon stick","10 black peppercorns","1 dried bay leaf","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","340 g dried cranberries","2 pinches fine salt","2 pinches black pepper, ground"]}],"id":"r126683","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-Uz-lLjQgQdo\/XZad4brzZtI\/AAAAAAAAggg\/p5YnVWLRi3IrvFaDdIfqK1t0V5EtkmCLgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_KZqx1CmL-rNM1gnL.png","title":"Cranberry and rosemary chutney","publishedAt":"2017-08-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"3 g","uom":"per 1 jar","carbohydrates":"227 g","calories":"3922 kJ \/ 936 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jars with twist-off lids","hintsAndTricks":["To ensure the chutney keeps for as long as possible, wash the jars thoroughly and dry in a warm oven or wash in the dishwasher. Transfer the chutney to the jars while they are still warm.","The cranberry and rosemary chutney keeps for up to <nobr>6 months<\/nobr> when unopened and stored in a cool, dry place.","If a smoother chutney is desired, chop <nobr><strong>5 sec\/speed 5<\/strong><\/nobr> at the end of step 4.","Serve the chutney with red meat, game dishes or flavoursome cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","45m","2 jars"]}